Heh, "accurate speed" is a very interesting term! But I guess you are right, the closer to 60 fps, the more accurate the speed is.<br /><br />When developing I try to get the I/O stuff out of the way first, and this is when emulator accuracy is most important. However, it has happened to me before that something that *shouldn't* be directly related to I/O broke some of the I/O logic. So I use Nintendulator and Nestopia during all my programming sessions, and every few days I test it on the PowerPak as well (even multiples times in a day if I'm doing something too hardcore that looks funky on emulators).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sun Dec 06, 2009 8:24 pm</p><hr />
